tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated total and LDL cholesterol, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Platelet count and platelet distribution width are also elevated, which may suggest reactive thrombocytosis or underlying inflammation but should be correlated clinically. Other hematological parameters are within normal limits. Lipid management and further evaluation of platelet abnormalities are recommended.
